<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?><news><article><URL><![CDATA[http://www.moneycontrol.com/news/features/what-is-gst-whatits-implicationssmall-businesses_9538161.html]]></URL><Heading><![CDATA[What is GST - What are its implications on Small Businesses?]]></Heading><Summary><![CDATA[By replacing numerous tax codes into one unified tax filing system, small businesses can take advantage of the time saved, by filing all returns under one tax code.]]></Summary><Body><![CDATA[<img src="http://livecms.moneycontrol.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/1.1-1-378x213.jpg" alt="GST (Goods and Services Tax) is the largest tax code reform in India, with an aim to enhance overall macro-economic growth. All businesses with a yearly turnover of 20 lakhs and above are now required to register under the GST network.  By replacing numerous tax codes into one unified tax filing system, small businesses can take advantage of the time saved, by filing all returns under one tax code.  The opportunity for growth is immense, and it has multiple benefits for small businesses in India.To get started, just register with www.gst.gov.in and follow the simple, user-friendly process to register your firm and get your GST ID. " width="378" height="213" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-2368605" /><p></p><img src="http://livecms.moneycontrol.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/1.2-1-378x213.jpg" alt="1 Tech Empowered - With more data and transparency brought in by GST, small businesses can simplify their filing process by embracing technology. Empowering your business with technology will greatly benefit you when you are filing on the GST portal, managing day-to-day operations and keeping a track of invoices. With the help of a personal computer, you can also be on top of execution and have more control over your business." width="378" height="213" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-2368611" /><p></p><img src="http://livecms.moneycontrol.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/1.3-1-378x213.jpg" alt="2 Data Protection â€“ With rising instances of hacking and fraud, businesses can protect their data by controlling it better. Sharing data with third-party vendors can be risky and data leaks may happen at any time. Now with self-filing facilities on the GST portal, you can use your own personal computer and protect your data. " width="378" height="213" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-2368613" /><p></p><img src="http://livecms.moneycontrol.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/1.4-1-378x213.jpg" alt="Ease of filing â€“ While filing GST monthly may seem cumbersome at first, a personal computer can make you more efficient in filing taxes online. You can track previous returns, manage future records, and ensure compliance with the regulations better. " width="378" height="213" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-2368615" /><p></p><img src="http://livecms.moneycontrol.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/1.5-1-378x213.jpg" alt="4 Managing cost â€“ There may be increased costs when filing through a third-party vendor, because of the new regulations under GST tax code. Small businesses can manage these costs by directly filing taxes through their computer. They can take advantage of the online platform provided by the government and file their returns without worry." width="378" height="213" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-2368617" /><p></p>]]></Body><Image><![CDATA[http://img-d01.moneycontrol.co.in/news_image_files/2017/356x200/2/2_356.jpg]]></Image><Entry_Date>2017-08-24 12:56:45</Entry_Date><Category>Features</Category><Video_flag>0</Video_flag></article></news>